s of the media but also shows how the story of electoral participation might be told in ways that support both democratic and journalistic values. At a time when professional strategists are pressuring journalists to provide favorable coverage for their causes and candidates, this book invites academics, organizations, the press, and citizens alike to advocate for the voter's place in the news.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJournalismxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aVoting researchzUnited States. 0aVotingzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Rhetoric.2bisacsh1 aHan, Soo-Hye, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311074522140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271082905?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271082905423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271082905/original  a978-3-11-074522-1  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK